history.content: I found it a worthwhile class. You can peruse through the current website (https://cs186berkeley.net/) now to see some of the topics covered. I think people find many of the topics a bit dry (there is little "flashy" things), but I found that the topics were quite still quite interesting. To give you my impression, the class goes is similar to 61B-like data-structures/algorithms in terms of doing things like joins, sorting, and indexing but combines this with more systems-like topics of disks, pages/buffers, and crash/recovery.

children.subject: I took the web-based version and thought that the module videos were a little boring, but straightforward. I'm glad I took the class though, because overall I think the material is useful.

history.content:
Next semester will be my last at Cal and I'm trying to figure out what to take before I leave. I'm likely doing 189, but was hoping to hear other people's thoughts on 186 since I don't personally know anybody who has taken it.

What did you like/not like/enjoy/find boring/etc? Would you recommend it to a friend? Not necessarily asking only about workload-wise since I likely won't have many techs next semester anyway, just want to gauge whether this class is something worth spending my time on for my last few months on campus. 

Thanks!
history.subject: Opinions on CS186
